Context:
The tab state system (tab-state.ts) computes plugin state and sends notifications via `notifyAffectedPlugins` → `computePluginTabState`. Two key spots where tab state is computed with full tab info:

1. `sendTabSyncAll` (tab-state.ts:190-259) — called after sync.full. Iterates all plugins, computes state, sends tab.syncAll to server. The `stateInfo` variable has `{ state: TabState, tabs: PluginTabInfo[] }`. At line 227: `lastKnownState.set(plugin.name, serializeTabState(stateInfo));`

2. `notifyAffectedPlugins` (tab-state.ts:367-390) — called from checkTabChanged and checkTabRemoved. At line 371: `const newState = await computePluginTabState(plugin);` — newState has `{ state, tabs }`. At line 383: `lastKnownState.set(plugin.name, serialized);`

In both spots, after updating lastKnownState, we should also persist the last-seen URL if the state is not 'closed'.

