Constraints:
- The `void` prefix is intentional — setLastSeenUrl is fire-and-forget, we do NOT want to await it in the hot tab-state path.
- Do NOT clear the URL when state becomes 'closed' — the whole point is to remember it.
- Do NOT modify PluginMeta or any wire protocol types — last-seen URL is extension-local state only.
- The in-memory cache avoids async reads on the hot path after initial load.
- Do NOT import last-seen-urls.ts in the side panel — it uses chrome.storage.local which is only available in the background script.

